This paper discusses the use of computational intelligence techniques for financial fraud detection, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also explores the effectiveness of different performance metrics and binary classification methods, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the specific problem of credit card fraud, which could be classified under the sub-category of cybercrime (cs.CY). Finally, the paper involves data analysis and experimentation, which could fall under the category of data science (cs.DS).
